------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party inspiration and acknowledgements
------------------------------------------------------------

The high-level multi-agent debate topology (analyst team → bull/bear
research debate → trader → 3-way risk debate → portfolio manager) is
inspired by:

  TauricResearch/TradingAgents — "TradingAgents: Multi-Agents LLM
  Financial Trading Framework", Apache-2.0 licensed.
  https://github.com/TauricResearch/TradingAgents

  Xiao et al., "TradingAgents: Multi-Agents LLM Financial Trading
  Framework", arXiv:2412.20138 (2025).
  https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.20138

TradingCrew is an independent implementation: it is built on CrewAI
(not LangGraph), introduces a deterministic post-LLM Layer-A pipeline
(M1–M7 — bridge, simulator, episodic memory, regime detector + critic,
sizer + gates, optional RL trainer), adds a futures dashboard with
cost-model presets, and ships its own FastAPI/WebSocket web UI. No
source code is copied from the upstream project.

